# Resolution 2003-04-01.wta.1: SPI fund management

April 1st, 2003

The following resolution has been accepted by the Board of Directors
of Software in the Public Interest, Inc.:

### WHEREAS:

1. Software in the Public Interest, Inc. (SPI) must pay certain expenses to
   to manage its resources and fulfill its functions; and
2. there is insufficient documentation regarding how donations made prior to
   January 2002 were earmarked;

RESOLVED THAT, five percent (5%) of the funds that SPI controlled in its AXP
Cash Management Account with American Express Financial Advisors as of 1
January 2002 shall be considered earmarked for SPI use;

FURTHER RESOLVED, that the remaining ninety-five percent (95%) of the funds
that SPI controlled in its AXP Cash Management Account with American Express
Financial Advisors as of 1 January 2002 shall be considered earmarked for the
Debian Project.

